tspan.tspan: (Objects Not To Scale)
Ditto, but with
Monitors/Webcams
facing inwards
I control the robot on the left, using "Fingers", which
broadcasts a 360 degree video stream of my head, including
audio out through speakers (me speaking). The webcams on
the robot also give me a 360 degree view of the robot's
position, and also has audio in through microphone (people/
aliens speaking).
The monitors/webcams can also be as tall as the human is
while standing and he can be on a never ending 360
degree conveyor belt and the robot can move in the
direction the human "walks".
The size of the robot and it's monitors is... irrelevant... in
fact the entire robot solution the to left is irrelevant... IF...
there is only robot 2 robot interaction (a room where there
are only robots... or in the long shot scenario where every
human uses one). This is of course ignoring the "interact
with scenery" counter-argument and is only dealing with
the robot 2 robot interaction. If there are no humans (or
scenery) to interact with (such as in an empty room), the
size and even existence of the robots is irrelevant and it
might as well be entirely virtual.
